<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en"><head>
<meta charset="utf-8"/>
<meta content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" name="viewport"/>
<title>Alien Civilization Calculator (Drake Equation)</title>
<meta content="Interactive Drake Equation calculator to estimate the number of active extraterrestrial civilizations in the Milky Way galaxy." name="description"/>
<meta content="Ugo Candido" name="author"/>
<link href="https://calcdomain.com/drake-equation.html" rel="canonical"/>
<style>
        :root {
            --primary-color: #005a9c;
            --background-color: #f8f9fa;
            --surface-color: #ffffff;
            --text-color: #212529;
            --border-color: #dee2e6;
            --danger-color: #dc3545;
            --success-color: #28a745;
        }
        body {
            font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
            background-color: var(--background-color);
            color: var(--text-color);
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }
        .container {
            max-width: 960px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 1rem;
        }
        .calculator-container {
            background-color: var(--surface-color);
            border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            border-radius: 8px;
            padding: 2rem;
            margin-top: 2rem;
        }
        .form-group {
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        }
        .form-group label {
            display: block;
            font-weight: 600;
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        }
        .form-control {
            width: 100%;
            padding: 0.75rem;
            font-size: 1rem;
            border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            border-radius: 6px;
        }
        .results-container {
            margin-top: 2rem;
            padding: 1.5rem;
            background: var(--background-color);
            border-radius: 8px;
            border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
        }
        .result-label {
            color: var(--text-color);
        }
        .result-value {
            font-weight: 700;
            font-size: 1.25rem;
            color: var(--success-color);
        }
        .content-container h2 {
            margin-top: 2rem;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
        }
    </style>
<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebPage",
  "name": "Alien Civilization Calculator (Drake Equation)",
  "description": "Interactive calculator to estimate the number of active extraterrestrial civilizations in the Milky Way galaxy using the Drake Equation.",
  "url": "https://calcdomain.com/drake-equation.html",
  "author": {
    "@type": "Person",
    "name": "Ugo Candido"
  },
  "publisher": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "Space Centre"
  }
}
  </script>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
<script src="search.js" defer></script>
<!-- MathJax for LaTeX formulas -->
<script>
  window.MathJax = {
    tex: {
      inlineMath: [['\(','\)'], ['$', '$']],
      displayMath: [['\[','\]']]
    },
    svg: { fontCache: 'global' }
  };
</script>
<script id="MathJax-script" async src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/mathjax@3/es5/tex-chtml.js"></script>
<link rel="preload" href="/assets/js/mobile-menu.js" as="script">
<link rel="preload" href="/assets/js/page-enhancements.js" as="script">

</head>
<body>

<header>
<h1>Alien Civilization Calculator (Drake Equation)</h1>
</header>
<main class="container">
<section>
<p>This calculator uses the Drake Equation to estimate the number of active extraterrestrial civilizations in the Milky Way galaxy. It's designed for astronomy enthusiasts and researchers interested in the search for extraterrestrial intelligence (SETI).</p>
</section>
<section aria-labelledby="calculator-heading" class="calculator-container">
<h2 id="calculator-heading">Drake Equation Calculator</h2>
<div class="form-group">
<label for="rateOfStarFormation">Rate of Star Formation (R*)</label>
<input aria-required="true" class="form-control" id="rateOfStarFormation" placeholder="e.g., 1.5" type="number"/>
</div>
<div class="form-group">
<label for="fractionOfStarsWithPlanets">Fraction of Stars with Planetary Systems (fp)</label>
<input aria-required="true" class="form-control" id="fractionOfStarsWithPlanets" placeholder="e.g., 0.5" type="number"/>
</div>
<div class="form-group">
<label for="planetsThatCanSupportLife">Average Number of Planets that Could Support Life (ne)</label>
<input aria-required="true" class="form-control" id="planetsThatCanSupportLife" placeholder="e.g., 2" type="number"/>
</div>
<div class="form-group">
<button aria-label="Calculate the number of civilizations" class="form-control" id="calculateButton">Calculate</button>
</div>
</section>
<section class="results-container">
<h3>Results</h3>
<div class="result-item">
<span class="result-label">Estimated Number of Civilizations</span>
<span class="result-value" id="estimatedCivilizations">0</span>
</div>
</section>
<section class="content-container">
<h2>Data Source and Methodology</h2>
<p>All calculations are based on the Drake Equation, formulated by Dr. Frank Drake in 1961. It is a probabilistic argument used to estimate the number of active, communicative extraterrestrial civilizations in the Milky Way galaxy. <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drake_equation" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Learn more about the Drake Equation.</a></p>
<h2>The Formula Explained</h2>
<p>The Drake Equation is: <span>N = R* × fp × ne × fl × fi × fc × L</span></p>
</section>
</main>

<script>
        document.getElementById('calculateButton').addEventListener('click', function () {
            const R = parseFloat(document.getElementById('rateOfStarFormation').value) || 0;
            const fp = parseFloat(document.getElementById('fractionOfStarsWithPlanets').value) || 0;
            const ne = parseFloat(document.getElementById('planetsThatCanSupportLife').value) || 0;
            const N = R * fp * ne;
            document.getElementById('estimatedCivilizations').textContent = N.toFixed(2);
        });
    </script>


```
